        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.76/6–446: Telegrams</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-28T20:00:00-04:00">June 28, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>885. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_desp1">desp</gloss>.
                    5216 June 4. It was Depts understanding Navy had requested you obtain extension
                    right to operate Recife radio direction finder station. If no action yet taken
                    pls approach <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss> Govt in effort obtain
                    consent, preferably in writing, to continued use this station for indefinite
                    period or for as long a time as possible.</p>
                <p>Chief Naval Operations has authorized Naval Attaché Rio abandon fixed
                    installations Belém and Bahia stations and you may support your request by
                    presenting these installations to <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss> Govt
                        (<gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> Airgram <gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss>–512 May 22<note n="47" xml:id="d400fn1">Not printed.</note>). Naval
                    Attaché has also been authorized declare equipment at Belém and Bahia stations
                    to <gloss target="#t_FLC1">FLC</gloss> as surplus. (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 847 June 24<note n="47" xml:id="d400fn2">Not
                    printed.</note>). Only if necessary to clinch right to continue operation at
                    Recife you are authorized arrange with <gloss target="#t_FLC1">FLC</gloss> Bio
                    for negotiation transfer this equipment to <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss>
                    Govt without cost but in this case Navy must arrange reimbursement to <gloss target="#t_FLC1">FLC</gloss> of appraised value equipment transferred.</p>
                <p>Consult with Gen. Miller<note n="48" xml:id="d400fn3">Representative of the
                        Foreign Liquidation Commission in Brazil.</note> as to desirability making
                    this approach prior conclusion of bulk sale.</p>
                <p>Keep Dept currently informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
